occurrenceRemarks: Hi Ian. Fabulous photo! The specimen is Pallenopsis macneilli Clark, 1963. The type locality is Nelsonâs Bay NSW but it is widely-spread along the s-e coast, southern coastline and Tas. I have it most often recorded from around the base of brown algae but I know exactly what its host substrate is. If you ever get the chance to photograph it in situ I would love to see it. It is always terrific to see these images. If nothing else it helps to plot the distribution of species. Good wishes and thanks for allowing me to see your photo ~David
Identification confirmed by David Staples, Sciences Department, Museum Victoria
